Text.Value: Erm, I think we weren't supposed to touch anything... right?

EditorData.AnimationTags: Custom Cine Anim work needed on [Machinery] and potentially [PLYR & Party], waiting on Cine feasability update. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player forcibly pulls the mace from the pedestal. Its light dims slightly.
EditorData.SFXTags: Interruption of energy hum and something mechanical drops into place releasing a large, heavy, wound up mechanisim

Text.Value: I'm all for looting sacred treasure, but only if I know I'll live long enough to enjoy it.
*You feel your patron's presence nearby. It hums with an unfamiliar anxiety.*
Step away. And banish this mace from your mind.
Be careful - the best cheese sits in the deadliest traps.
We should leave that thing and just get out of here while we can.
Are you quite sure that's wise? We should leave this untouched and get out of here.
*Taking such a holy weapon would be diabolical indeed, but the consequences... disastrous.*
*Snatching a holy weapon from a godly dungeon would be mischevious indeed, but the consequences... disastrous.*
*To take the god-weapon - to humiliate divinity - would be satisfying. But it would risk disastrous ruin.*
*This mace certainly has a very unusual design.*
Take the mace anyway - what's the worst that could happen?
We should leave this untouched and get out of here.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The hinges on the floor unlock in quick succession and a ring in the floor rotates with a mechanical jolt.

Companions step back from it as the player looks around, concerned. The ring swiftly rises from the floor, pulling up a forcefield barrier with it.
EditorData.SFXTags: Heavy metal locks releasing, heavy metal ring grinding and mechanisim, barrier energy starting up
EditorData.VFXTags: Barrier energy field, dust around machine elements as they kick back into life

Text.Value: You sure about that? Not every glowing light is an invitation to take what's inside it.
*An ornate mace hovers before you, suspended in a shaft of brilliant light.*

EditorData.VFXTags: Glow emitting from the amboer piece in mace

Text.Value: Hells - I don't like the look of that. Run, damn it, run!
Reach into the light and take the mace.
Not one to heed warnings then? We should leave that thing - it seems like trouble.
*A fist-sized piece of amber flecked with crimson is set in the handle, emitting a radiance all its own.*
Might be better to leave it alone. No sense tempting trouble.

EditorData.logicalname: Check more than one party member

Text.Value: Leave it be. Not every glowing light is an invitation take what's inside it.
*The brutal aches in your body yearn to take it, though you sense it will spell misfortune.*
*Everything is in motion - all within these walls are doomed to destruction unless you act.*
Resist the call to the dark: leave the mace be.
Better leave the mace where it is for now.
Not one to heed warning then? This could end very badly.
Claim the mace and delight in its danger.
*The glow around the mace sparkles with beautiful disaster.*
You sure about that, soldier? Seems risky.
The crche is done for, but we're not. Run! Run damn you!

EditorData.NodeContext: Room starting to collapse around the party

Text.Value: Hang on - what's going on? Stop this, before it's too late!
I think this crche's days are numbered - let's get out of here.
Are you sure about that? This all feels very... trappy.
Leave the mace where it is.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The player looks up as the static gyro rings above their head shudder into life, slowly rotating independently.

Pillars rise from the darkness. As each pillar locks into place, one of the four gyro rings locks with its crystal pointing toward the pillar followed by the pillar crystal illuminating.

A glow forms in the middle of the gyro as a portal opens in the doorway, a beam of light then shooting out of the gyros glow straight through the portal.
EditorData.SFXTags: Trap and mechanisim SFXs as listed in kick-off/taskgroup - Pillars rising, Light crystals/ beams activating, gyro spining up, portal doorway activating, dust/ debris falling
EditorData.VFXTags: Trap and mechanisim VFXs as listed in kick-off/taskgroup - Lightcrystals, light beams, gyro glow, portal doorway, dust/ debris falling

Text.Value: *This mace must be the legendary Blood of Lathander - the amber is said to contain the blood of the Morninglord himself.*
Are you quite sure that's wise?
You heard the warnings. Are you sure you want to stick your hand where it wasn't invited?
Stay your hand! The consequences may be more than we are ready to bear.
*You stand before the mysterious mace once more.*

EditorData.VFXTags: Glow emitting from the amboer piece in mace

Text.Value: *Taking this mace would surely lead to something quite disastrous.*
*You recall all the measures meant to keep you from reaching this place.*
Stay your hand! The consequences may be more than we are ready to bear.
Tsk'va - what have you done? Shut it down before the crche is made rubble!

Synopsis: The player decides if they should take The Blood of Lathander (the Sun Mace). Taking it will cause the destruction of the monastery (and the gith crche within it).
